main event: On October 23, 1957, in Corpus Christi, Texas, three round, luminous, yellow objects in a 'V' formation were observed traveling in a straight line for 3 - 5 seconds.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a car and left behind a luminous trail.
The report included photographs of the objects.
The observation was made by a civilian.
The sighting was initially evaluated as a meteor sighting.
The report suggested that the sighting could have been a misinterpretation of natural phenomena or an overly active imagination.
sighted object: three round, luminous, yellow objects in a 'V' formation
